6// MemoryProgramCache: Stores compiled and linked programs in memory so they don't
7// always have to be re-compiled. Can be used in conjunction with the platform
8// layer to warm up the cache from disk.

32constexpr unsigned int kWarningLimit = 3;
33
34class HashStream final : angle::NonCopyable
35{
36 public:
37 std::string str() { return mStringStream.str(); }
38
39 template <typename T>
40 HashStream &operator<<(T value)
41 {
42 mStringStream << value << kSeparator;
43 return *this;
44 }
45
46 private:
47 static constexpr char kSeparator = ':';
48 std::ostringstream mStringStream;
49};
50
51HashStream &operator<<(HashStream &stream, const Shader *shader)
52{
53 if (shader)
54 {
55 stream << shader->getSourceString().c_str() << shader->getSourceString().length()
56 << shader->getCompilerResourcesString().c_str();
57 }
58 return stream;
59}
60
61HashStream &operator<<(HashStream &stream, const ProgramBindings &bindings)
62{
63 for (const auto &binding : bindings)
64 {
65 stream << binding.first << binding.second;
66 }
67 return stream;
68}
69
70HashStream &operator<<(HashStream &stream, const ProgramAliasedBindings &bindings)
71{
72 for (const auto &binding : bindings)
73 {
74 stream << binding.first << binding.second.location;
75 }
76 return stream;
77}
78
79HashStream &operator<<(HashStream &stream, const std::vector<std::string> &strings)
80{
81 for (const auto &str : strings)
82 {
83 stream << str;
84 }
85 return stream;
86}
87
88HashStream &operator<<(HashStream &stream, const std::vector<gl::VariableLocation> &locations)
89{
90 for (const auto &loc : locations)
91 {
92 stream << loc.index << loc.arrayIndex << loc.ignored;
93 }
94 return stream;
95}
96
97} // anonymous namespace

99MemoryProgramCache::MemoryProgramCache(egl::BlobCache &blobCache)
100 : mBlobCache(blobCache), mIssuedWarnings(0)
101{}
102
103MemoryProgramCache::~MemoryProgramCache() {}
104
105void MemoryProgramCache::ComputeHash(const Context *context,
106 const Program *program,
107 egl::BlobCache::Key *hashOut)
108{
109 // Compute the program hash. Start with the shader hashes and resource strings.
110 HashStream hashStream;
111 for (ShaderType shaderType : AllShaderTypes())
112 {
113 hashStream << program->getAttachedShader(shaderType);
114 }
115
116 // Add some ANGLE metadata and Context properties, such as version and back-end.
117 hashStream << ANGLE_COMMIT_HASH << context->getClientMajorVersion()
118 << context->getClientMinorVersion() << context->getString(GL_RENDERER);
119
120 // Hash pre-link program properties.
121 hashStream << program->getAttributeBindings() << program->getUniformLocationBindings()
122 << program->getFragmentOutputLocations() << program->getFragmentOutputIndexes()
123 << program->getState().getTransformFeedbackVaryingNames()
124 << program->getState().getTransformFeedbackBufferMode()
125 << program->getState().getOutputLocations()
126 << program->getState().getSecondaryOutputLocations();
127
128 // Call the secure SHA hashing function.
129 const std::string &programKey = hashStream.str();
130 angle::base::SHA1HashBytes(reinterpret_cast<const unsigned char *>(programKey.c_str()),
131 programKey.length(), hashOut->data());
132}
133
134angle::Result MemoryProgramCache::getProgram(const Context *context,
135 Program *program,
136 egl::BlobCache::Key *hashOut)
137{
138 // If caching is effectively disabled, don't bother calculating the hash.
139 if (!mBlobCache.isCachingEnabled())
140 {
141 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
142 }
143
144 ComputeHash(context, program, hashOut);
145 egl::BlobCache::Value binaryProgram;
146 size_t programSize = 0;
147 if (get(context, *hashOut, &binaryProgram, &programSize))
148 {
149 uint32_t uncompressedSize =
150 zlib_internal::GetGzipUncompressedSize(binaryProgram.data(), programSize);
151
152 std::vector<uint8_t> uncompressedData(uncompressedSize);
153 uLong destLen = uncompressedSize;
154 int zResult = zlib_internal::GzipUncompressHelper(uncompressedData.data(), &destLen,
155 binaryProgram.data(),
156 static_cast<uLong>(programSize));
157
158 if (zResult != Z_OK)
159 {
160 ERR() << "Failure to decompressed binary data: " << zResult << "\n";
161 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
162 }
163
164 angle::Result result =
165 program->loadBinary(context, GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_ANGLE, uncompressedData.data(),
166 static_cast<int>(uncompressedData.size()));
167 ANGLE_HISTOGRAM_BOOLEAN("GPU.ANGLE.ProgramCache.LoadBinarySuccess",
168 result == angle::Result::Continue);
169 ANGLE_TRY(result);
170
171 if (result == angle::Result::Continue)
172 return angle::Result::Continue;
173
174 // Cache load failed, evict.
175 if (mIssuedWarnings++ < kWarningLimit)
176 {
177 WARN() << "Failed to load binary from cache.";
178
179 if (mIssuedWarnings == kWarningLimit)
180 {
181 WARN() << "Reaching warning limit for cache load failures, silencing "
182 "subsequent warnings.";
183 }
184 }
185 remove(*hashOut);
186 }
187 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
188}

190bool MemoryProgramCache::get(const Context *context,
191 const egl::BlobCache::Key &programHash,
192 egl::BlobCache::Value *programOut,
193 size_t *programSizeOut)
194{
195 return mBlobCache.get(context->getScratchBuffer(), programHash, programOut, programSizeOut);
196}

198bool MemoryProgramCache::getAt(size_t index,
199 const egl::BlobCache::Key **hashOut,
200 egl::BlobCache::Value *programOut)
201{
202 return mBlobCache.getAt(index, hashOut, programOut);
203}

205void MemoryProgramCache::remove(const egl::BlobCache::Key &programHash)
206{
207 mBlobCache.remove(programHash);
208}
209
210angle::Result MemoryProgramCache::putProgram(const egl::BlobCache::Key &programHash,
211 const Context *context,
212 const Program *program)
213{
214 // If caching is effectively disabled, don't bother serializing the program.
215 if (!mBlobCache.isCachingEnabled())
216 {
217 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
218 }
219
220 angle::MemoryBuffer serializedProgram;
221 ANGLE_TRY(program->serialize(context, &serializedProgram));
222
223 // Compress the program data
224 uLong uncompressedSize = static_cast<uLong>(serializedProgram.size());
225 uLong expectedCompressedSize = zlib_internal::GzipExpectedCompressedSize(uncompressedSize);
226
227 angle::MemoryBuffer compressedData;
228 if (!compressedData.resize(expectedCompressedSize))
229 {
230 ERR() << "Failed to allocate enough memory to hold compressed program. ("
231 << expectedCompressedSize << " bytes )";
232 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
233 }
234
235 int zResult = zlib_internal::GzipCompressHelper(compressedData.data(), &expectedCompressedSize,
236 serializedProgram.data(), uncompressedSize,
237 nullptr, nullptr);
238
239 if (zResult != Z_OK)
240 {
241 FATAL() << "Error compressing binary data: " << zResult;
242 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
243 }
244
245 // Resize the buffer to the actual compressed size
246 if (!compressedData.resize(expectedCompressedSize))
247 {
248 ERR() << "Failed to resize to actual compressed program size. (" << expectedCompressedSize
249 << " bytes )";
250 return angle::Result::Incomplete;
251 }
252
253 ANGLE_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS("GPU.ANGLE.ProgramCache.ProgramBinarySizeBytes",
254 static_cast<int>(compressedData.size()));
255
256 // TODO(syoussefi): to be removed. Compatibility for Chrome until it supports
257 // EGL_ANDROID_blob_cache. http://anglebug.com/2516
258 auto *platform = ANGLEPlatformCurrent();
259 platform->cacheProgram(platform, programHash, compressedData.size(), compressedData.data());
260
261 mBlobCache.put(programHash, std::move(compressedData));
262 return angle::Result::Continue;
263}
264
265angle::Result MemoryProgramCache::updateProgram(const Context *context, const Program *program)
266{
267 egl::BlobCache::Key programHash;
268 ComputeHash(context, program, &programHash);
269 return putProgram(programHash, context, program);
270}
271
272bool MemoryProgramCache::putBinary(const egl::BlobCache::Key &programHash,
273 const uint8_t *binary,
274 size_t length)
275{
276 // Copy the binary.
277 angle::MemoryBuffer newEntry;
278 if (!newEntry.resize(length))
279 {
280 return false;
281 }
282 memcpy(newEntry.data(), binary, length);
283
284 // Store the binary.
285 mBlobCache.populate(programHash, std::move(newEntry));
286
287 return true;
288}
289
290void MemoryProgramCache::clear()
291{
292 mBlobCache.clear();
293 mIssuedWarnings = 0;
294}
295
296void MemoryProgramCache::resize(size_t maxCacheSizeBytes)
297{
298 mBlobCache.resize(maxCacheSizeBytes);
299}
